The paper proposes approximation strategies for improving incomplete MaxSAT solving, which involves finding a solution that minimizes the sum of weights of unsatisfied soft clauses without providing any optimality guarantees. This problem is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves finding an optimal solution. The paper also involves clustering and breaking up the problem into subproblems, which are techniques commonly used in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves optimization (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC) as it deals with finding better solutions than the best incomplete solvers.
